oai_dc:dc.dc:title: agapornis acres: THE BLACK-CHEEKED (Agapornis nigrigensis) AND THE NYASSALAND (Agapornis lilianae)
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Horton, Lee
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Two birds that should be as commonas the Black Masked (agapomis personata)and the Fischer's (agapornis fischeri)in the United States are the Black Cheeked(a. nigrigensis) and the Nyassaland(a. lilianae). However, neither of theseLovebirds are well established. The Nyassalandis seen in very few aviaries andthe Black-cheeked is a true rarity inaviaries. Yet both birds breed well andshould be as easy as any other in the eyering group .
